Justice Chioma Nwosu-Iheme of the Benin Division of the Court of Appeal, has regained her freedom. DAILY POST had reported that suspected gunmen on Wednesday last week in Benin City, capital of Edo State, abducted Justice Chioma Nwosu-Iheme of the Court of Appeal, Benin Division The Commissioner of Police, Edo Command, Danmallam Mohammed confirmed the release of the judge Mohammed told Channels TV that Judge Nwosu-Iheme has since been reunited with her family. DAILY POST recalls that the Nigerian Bar Association, Benin branch, had embarked on a three-day boycott of all courts last week following her abduction. Details later.. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.